etymologies: late 17th century: from French décile, from a medieval Latin derivative of Latin decem ‘ten’

definitions: each of ten equal groups into which a population can be divided according to the distribution of values of a particular variable

examples.text: the lowest income decile of the population

shortDefinitions: each of ten equal groups into which population can be divided according to distribution of values of particular variable

definitions: each of the nine values of the random variable that divide a population into ten such groups.
shortDefinitions: each of nine values of random variable which divide population into ten such groups
